This Java code defines a method `isPalindrome` that takes a `String` as an argument and returns `true` if the string is a palindrome and `false` otherwise. It compares characters from opposite ends of the string until the middle is reached or a mismatch is found.

### C++ Implementation:
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;

bool isPalindrome(const string &str) {
    int i = 0, j = str.length() - 1;
    while (i < j) {
        if (str[i] != str[j])
            return false;
        i++;
        j--;
    }
    return true;
}

int main() {
    string str = "racecar"; // Example string
